= 78 + 165 + 130 + 494 + 851 = 1 718

Wheat and Wood are below-average value for me; they are good trade-ballast.

[Offer: 3 Wheat, 5 Wood -> 2 Brick]

I notice I’ve burned four turns proposing trades without any counter-offers or bargaining from Player 0, and every one has been denied.

My best value-to-quantity ratio resource is Ore (37 value / 23 units ≈ 1.61 per unit); my worst is Wheat (6 value / 13 units ≈ 0.46 per unit). I need to move value into the higher-valued resource class while still keeping each resource type diversified enough to function.

Therefore, I’ll offer a package that over-delivers value to Player 0 so it’s hard to refuse, while I gain net value overall by shifting low-value Wheat and Wood into higher-value Brick, Ore and Sheep.

[Offer: 4 Wheat, 6 Wood, 2 Sheep -> 5 Ore, 2 Brick]
